{{Constitutions of Poland}}
'''Small Constitution of 1947''' ({{lang-pl|Mała Konstytucja z 1947}}) was a temporary [[constitution]] issued by the [[communist]]-dominated [[Sejm]] (Polish parliament) [[Sejm Ustawodawczy (1947&ndash;1952)|of 1947&ndash;1952]]. It confirmed the practice of [[separation of powers]] and strengthened the Sejm. It was renewed in 1949, 1950 and 1951. It recognized some articles of the previous [[March Constitution of Poland]] (1921) and [[PKWN Manifesto]] (1944), whereas the [[April Constitution of Poland|Constitution of 1935]] was declared null and void as [[fascism|fascist]]. It was replaced in 1952 by the [[Constitution of the People's Republic of Poland]].

